Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/5-218113e/feedback.md`. Here's the summary:

**4 themes across the 3 failures:**

1. **Structural bonus leaks into threshold** (cases 2 & 3): `structuralBonus (+0.10)` is included in `baseScore`, which drives the `bestBaseScore × 0.7` threshold up. Correct titles lacking the structural bonus fall below the inflated bar — the exact same problem the code tried to fix for position bias, but not fixed for bonuses.

2. **"Shorter wins" dedup destroys multi-line joins** (cases 1 & 3): The dedup rule removes a candidate if a shorter substring also exists. The first line of a split title is always a substring of the 2-line join, so the join — the only correct answer — gets discarded.

3. **Garbled OCR passes `isStructuralHeading`** (case 3): `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` satisfies all structural checks (ALL_CAPS, ≥2 sig words, each ≥4 letters) despite being a truncated OCR artifact. It hijacks the `baseHeading` role, getting +0.18 in bonuses, while also preventing the continuation-extension logic from firing for the real title on lines 54–55.

4. **Mixed-case titles get no bonuses and may not clear the 0.08 floor** (case 1): No `allCapsBonus`, no `structuralBonus`, and the title is split across lines where dedup removes the join — leaving nothing above threshold.
