lt was just \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\". Let me work through the scoring to see if the threshold is filtering out the second item. If I estimate \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\" has a rawScore around 0.08, that gives a baseScore of 0.26 and a threshold of 0.182. Meanwhile \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" would have a rawScore of 0.10, which falls below that threshold and gets eliminated.\n\nSo the structural heading bonus on the wrong candidate inflates the threshold just enough to reject the correct title. And the continuation logic that should've promoted \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D\" didn't trigger either.\n\nThe problem is that the continuation logic relies on `baseHeading` being the actual first line of the title, but here the garbled candidate \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\" won that role instead. So when the logic tries to extend the correct title with the continuation character, it's checking against the wrong base heading and never finds a match.\n\nThis reveals the core issue: the deduplication logic removes longer candidates when they contain a shorter one, which means split titles get truncated to just their first line. That partial line then becomes the `baseHeading`, blocking both the direct scoring and the continuation extension for the complete title. Structural bonus inflation of threshold (cases 2 and 3): The structural heading bonus (+0.10) on an incorrect or partial candidate raises `bestBaseScore`, which raises the threshold via `bestBaseScore * 0.7`, potentially excluding the correct title from passing the threshold.\n\nGarbled OCR lines becoming structural headings (case 3): \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\" - a truncated OCR artifact - passes `isStructuralHeading` because it looks structurally valid (all caps, multi-word, all sig words ≥ 4 letters). This causes the wrong candidate to get the structural bonus and become `firstStructuralHeading`.\n\nContinuation extension fails for correct titles (case 3): The continuation logic to promote 2-line title joins only works when `baseHeading` IS the correct title's first line. When a wrong candidate becomes `baseHeading`, the continuation logic never fires for the real title.\n\nMixed-case titles have no bonus (case 1): The ALL_CAPS bonus and structural bonus only apply to ALL_CAPS titles. Mixed-case titles like \"Baked Eggs with Feta...\" have no bonus, and combined with the floor threshold of 0.08, they may fail to pass.\n\nSplit title and short-wins deduplication (case 1): The deduplication removes the full 2-line join in favor of the shorter partial line, leaving neither option matching the expected title exactly. Now I'm writing up this analysis in the feedback file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10699,"cache_read_input_tokens":19856,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10699},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89da370b-71e2-4fdf-ac53-b3797a019eb5","uuid":"4811bad5-31ec-406c-8e3c-b568db65da14"}
